31/01/2005
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Boris Miksic, the former independent candidate for president, announced on Sunday (30 January) that he would run for mayor of Zagreb in May.
Miksic, who has a successful business in the United States, said he would remain in politics because of his surprisingly strong showing in the presidential race.
He placed third in the first round.
(HRT - 30/01/05;
Vecernji list - 28/01/05)
